data.title: Preston Dermatology & Dr. Sheel Desai Solomon win top Awards in Raleigh's Best from The News & Observer. Dr. Solomon named Best Doctor.
data.description: In a recent announcement, it was revealed that Dr. Sheel Desai Solomon and Preston Dermatology and Skin Surgery Center, P.A. dominated The News & Observer's Raleigh's Best Annual Awards. Dr. Solomon clinched the top spot with a Gold award for Best Doctor. The prestigious accolade highlights the exceptional medical service provided by Dr. Solomon. This recognition underscores the trust and esteem in which Dr. Solomon is held within the community. Preston Dermatology and Skin Surgery Center, P.A. also received commendation, further solidifying their reputation for excellence in healthcare.

data.title: Vivakor sets new payment date for special dividend to Dec 31, 2025 due to government shutdown. Ex-dividend date was Sept 5, 2025.
data.description: In Dallas, TX, on October 31, 2025, Vivakor, Inc. (Nasdaq: VIVK), a company offering energy transportation, storage, reuse, and remediation services, has rescheduled the payment date for its special dividend to shareholders to December 31, 2025. The ex-dividend date was September 5, 2025. This change was made to allow for necessary communication and filings with the Securities and Exchange Commission, which cannot be completed during the current government shutdown. There is a possibility of further delays to the special dividend if the shutdown persists.

data.title: UNI OI drops 50% below moving averages. Uniswap at $5.71 with open interest down from $300M to $140M, reflecting cautious sentiment despite stable crypto market.
data.description: The trading price of Uniswap is currently at $5.71, which comes amidst a decrease in speculative trading. The open interest on the platform has also fallen significantly from $300 million to $140 million. This shift indicates a sense of caution in the market, despite the overall stability in the cryptocurrency sector.

data.title: Info-Tech Research Group provides blueprint for CJIS compliance amid struggling law enforcement agencies modernizing IT systems.
data.description: Numerous law enforcement and government organizations are facing challenges in meeting the continually changing CJIS security requirements as they upgrade their IT systems. A leading global research and advisory firm, Info-Tech Research Group, has unveiled a new blueprint called Build a CJIS Compliance Program. This blueprint aims to assist organizations in aligning with CJIS security mandates. It offers comprehensive guidance on establishing effective compliance measures.

data.title: Many workers won't receive raises in 2025; 25% promoted without pay increase; 50% companies anticipate layoffs in 2026.
data.description: A recent survey of 1,000 U.S. business leaders revealed that 25% of companies promoted employees without a salary increase. Additionally, nearly 50% of the surveyed leaders anticipate layoffs in 2026. These findings were reported by Resume.org, a prominent resume-building platform, in Kirkland, Wash., on October 31, 2025.

data.title: Dickinson College receives $20 million donation to establish "Jim Thorpe Center" addressing Native American boarding school history.
data.description: On October 31, 2025, in Carlisle, Pennsylvania, Dickinson College will establish the "Jim Thorpe Center for the Futures of Native Peoples" near the former site of the Carlisle Indian Industrial School (CIIS). CIIS, the first federally funded off-reservation boarding school in the United States, was created with the objective of forcibly assimilating Native American children and youth to "kill the Indian... save the man." The new center represents a powerful healing and corrective initiative.

data.title: Pure Romance, the leading sexual wellness brand, hosts a 12-hour live shopping marathon on November 4 for National Sex Toy Day.
data.description: On October 31, 2025, in Cincinnati, Pure Romance, the leading brand in sexual wellness and intimacy globally, announced plans to mark National Sex Toy Day with a 12-hour live shopping event on November 4. The marathon will be streamed from 12 PM ET to Midnight solely on PureRomance.com. The broadcast will feature a range of products and special deals, catering to their audience's needs and preferences.

data.title: Chainlink prices rise to $16.99 after 2.5% increase as whales accumulate $188M worth of LINK tokens, showing institutional support.
data.description: Trading at $16.99, the cryptocurrency LINK has experienced a 2.5% increase in value. This surge follows the withdrawal of approximately 10 million tokens from the exchange Binance by a large investor, suggesting strong institutional faith in the digital asset.

data.description: The price of Polkadot stands at $2.86 after the SEC delays the decision on 21Shares DOT ETF. Technical analysis indicates a possible turnaround from oversold levels in the market.

data.title: Hernandez Homes LLC thriving with a successful Q3 2025, eyes expansion with fixer-uppers in AZ; specializes in improving residential properties for neighborhood revitalization.
data.description: A real estate investment company based in Arizona, Hernandez Homes LLC, has shown consistent growth in the first three quarters of 2025. Since its establishment in February 2024, the company has focused on renovating residential properties in Maricopa, Pinal, and Coconino Counties. By specializing in acquiring and enhancing underutilized homes, Hernandez Homes LLC aims to rejuvenate neighborhoods and create lasting value. Their success is evident through multiple completed fixer-upper projects and a continued strong deal flow.

data.description: For numerous years, the cable channel continuously aired reruns of the comedy clip show, a tactic that was adopted by other cable networks as well.

data.title: Court orders Trump admin to pay SNAP benefits during shutdown, preventing millions of low-income Americans from losing benefits.
data.description: Lawsuits were filed by states, cities, and nonprofits in an effort to prevent millions of low-income individuals from losing benefits set to begin on Saturday. The Trump administration announced it would cease funding, prompting legal action to protect those affected.

data.title: AVAX tests $17.92 with 10% institutional investment surge amid Bitcoin correlation test, facing mixed technical signals.
data.description: Following a 10% surge in institutional investment, Avalanche (AVAX) is currently trading at $17.92. However, the recent downturn in Bitcoin is putting pressure on AVAX's price resilience. The cryptocurrency is facing mixed technical signals amidst this volatility.
